Tasks - 
    Utilize CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete)
    
    Create - 
        make the form in CreateTask.js a controlled form
        Use the data from the form to create a fetch POST request that will create a task in the db
        Make sure that the data is persisted to the db and the tasks are updated in the browser

    Read - 
        Create a search bar to search for certain tasks/categories of tasks
        Display the results in the taskBlock

    Update -
        Each task will be clickable
        When a task is clicked, it will open a form to update the task
        Once submitted, the data from the form will be persisted to db, and the task will update without refreshing the page

    Delete -
        Click on the delete button to delete a task
        Display a message that the task has been succesfuly deleted